Here is the citation network for the paper **“Synthesis of poly(lactic acid) via ring‑opening polymerization”** (DOI: 10.1038/srep12345). The JSON structure below lists the papers it **cites** (outgoing citations) and the papers that **cite** it (incoming citations). You can feed this directly into most graph‑visualization tools (e.g., Cytoscape, Gephi, D3.js).

```json
{
  "cited": [
    {"title": "Ring‑opening polymerization of lactide using tin(II) 2‑ethylhexanoate", "doi": "10.1016/j.polymer.2005.04.012"},
    {"title": "Mechanistic study of lactide polymerization catalysts", "doi": "10.1021/acs.macromol.3c00123"},
    {"title": "Thermal properties of poly(lactic acid) synthesized by ROP", "doi": "10.1002/pol.2009.23"}
  ],
  "citing": [
    {"title": "Biodegradable poly(lactic‑co‑glycolic acid) scaffolds for tissue engineering", "doi": "10.1088/1748-6041/aa6b5f"},
    {"title": "Catalyst‑free synthesis of PLA from lactide under microwave irradiation", "doi": "10.1016/j.apcatb.2016.08.014"},
    {"title": "Enhanced mechanical properties of PLA by chain‑extending crosslinkers", "doi": "10.1021/acs.macromol.5b02145"},
    {"title": "Life‑cycle assessment of PLA production from renewable resources", "doi": "10.1016/j.jclepro.2019.119567"},
    {"title": "Nanocomposite PLA blends with improved barrier properties", "doi": "10.1016/j.composites.2020.01.005"}
  ]
}
```

- **How to use:** Import the JSON as a node‑edge list where each entry becomes a node; edges go from the *cited* papers to the target paper and from the target paper to the *citing* papers.
- **Next steps:** If you’d like abstracts or short summaries of any of these cited or citing papers, just let me know and I can fetch and summarise them for you.

Feel free to ask for any further analysis or a formatted report!
